  "body": "### Description\n\nAs discussed on [Quarkus dev](https://groups.google.com/g/quarkus-dev/c/AnJLtYwgQxs/m/pYr1njhCAgAJ), I would like to have a way to disable datasources at runtime. Currently, this is not possible, I have tried defining different datasources for each flavor, but this still means that the datasource is created for the unused flavours, so I guess it still has some impact. I know that I can remove the unused datasource from the health checks, but I'm assuming (at least that's what I saw in my testing) that the beans are still created.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nEssentially, what I'm asking for is something similar to https://quarkus.io/version/main/guides/hibernate-orm#quarkus-hibernate-orm_quarkus.hibernate-orm.active but for the datasource itself.",
